Damaturu- The Senior Staff Association of Nigeria Polytechnics (SSANIP) on Monday issued a 14-day ultimatum to the authorities concerned to respond to the demands of it’s members or shut down Federal Polytechnic, Damaturu in Yobe State. This was contained in a letter dated 4th December, 2021 jointly signed by the branch Chairman, Muhammad Nura Nguru and branch Secretary, Adamu Adamu made available to Daily Independent in Damaturu. The letter reads “The Senior Staff Association of Nigeria Polytechnics (SSANIP), the Federal Polytechnic Damaturu has today commenced 14-days warning strike from 4th January, 2021.” ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! “This is in line with the resolutions adopted at the 62nd regular meeting of the Union held monthly at the labour house, Abuja”. According to them, the action was initiated to address their lingering demands with the Federal government. Ibidapo-Obe: Nigeria Lost University Administrator Of Special Ilk- Okebukola Edo NUT Directs Primary School Teachers To Shun Enrollment Into State Government Pension Scheme Such demands they enumerated include the re-evaluation and implementation of assessment report, release of scheme of service for the Polytechnic by the National Board for Technical Education (NBTE), non payment of complete salaries and arrears of minimum wage. Others are the lingering issues associated with the Integrated Personal Payroll Integrated System (IPPIS), constitution of the Governing Councils in the Federal Polytechnics. They indicated that at the expiration of the strike, the union shall find ways of reviewing the situation. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION